# Bash Component Patterns

- Keep scripts Bash-first and consistent with nearby files; avoid introducing heavier tooling for simple install steps.
- Name **all Bash functions in camelCase** (no `snake_case` or leading underscores); match helpers in [`src/`](/src/) (e.g. `registerBuildMetadata`, `showUsage`, `ensureShellRcRegion`, `ensureWslConfIniLine`, `getFile`, `printInfo`).
- **`conf.sh`** calls **`registerBuildMetadata`** (`src/build-metadata.sh`): `BUILD_DIR_NAME`, `BUILD_VER`, CSV of valid components, `NUM_ADDITIONAL_ARGS`. **`ai-resources`**: optional **`AI_RESOURCES_PROJECT_DIR`** in user **`wsl-builds.conf`**; **`conf.sh`** sets **`PROJECT_DIR`** (default **`$HOME/ai-resources`**) for **`install_<component>.sh`**.
- Add new components to the third argument CSV. Use names that round-trip to **`install_<underscore_name>.sh`** (hyphens in the CSV become underscores in filenames: `mysql-client` → `install_mysql_client.sh`).
- **`install.sh`** is only **`source "${TOOL_DIR}/src/install-dispatch.sh"`**. The dispatch loop runs **at top level** inside **`src/install-dispatch.sh`** (no wrapper function) so **`./wsl-builder.sh`** (**the builder**) remains the supported entrypoint and `$@` propagates when `install.sh` is sourced. Keep `install.sh` free of duplicated `if` blocks.
- **`~/.bashrc` / `~/.zshrc`:** use **`ensureShellRcRegion`**, **`replaceManagedShellRcRegion`**, or **`removeManagedShellRcRegion`** from [`src/shell-rc.sh`](../../src/shell-rc.sh) (named `wsl-builds:<id>` blocks) instead of one-off `grep` + `>>`.
- **`/etc/wsl.conf`:** use **`ensureWslConfIniLine`** from [`src/wsl-conf.sh`](../../src/wsl-conf.sh) for add-only, idempotent section lines (with `sudo`).
- Put component logic in **`install_<component>.sh`** (underscore filename as above).
- **apt (Ubuntu):** run `sudo apt update` before repo-backed `sudo apt install`; always pass `-y`; use `apt` not `apt-get`. Skip `apt update` for local `.deb` / `dpkg -i` only. Snippet: `printInfo "Installing X"` → `sudo apt update` → `sudo apt install -y …` → optional version line → `printInfo "X installed"`.
- **Component messaging** — user-visible status should be consistent and easy to scan:
  - **Open** with one line: `printInfo "Installing <Name>"` (human-readable product name; use the same noun in the closing line).
  - **In progress:** step `printInfo` lines have no ellipsis (`…` / `...`).
  - **Close** with one final line: `printInfo "<Name> installed"` — past tense, no "successfully", no ellipsis, no trailing period. Must be the **last** user-facing status (after any verification).
  - **Channels:** use `printInfo`, `printWarning`, and `printError` for step/status output. Use `echo` only for data written into files or heredocs, not for install progress.
  - **Optional:** if a natural version command exists, prefer `printInfo "<Name> version: $(cmd …)"` (or the first line of output) instead of raw `--version` stdout as the script’s last impression. No `2>/dev/null || echo …` fallbacks.
  - **Golden example:** [`builds/dev-js/install_node.sh`](../../builds/dev-js/install_node.sh).
  - **`Tests`** — Changing literal **`print*`** strings (or any fixed user-visible lines) often breaks **`test/docker/*.bats`** regex/substring checks. **`rg`** **`test/`** and **`builds/test-fixture/`** for fragments of the old wording and refresh assertions/fixtures **in the same change** when you reshape output; run **`./test/run-tests.sh`** after edits to **`src/`** helpers or **`./wsl-builder.sh`** messaging.
- **Optional: disable start on boot (systemd)** — Vendor installers or packages may **`systemctl enable`** a daemon. In WSL, many users prefer not to run background services at every boot. After the substantive install (and before **`printInfo "<Name> installed"`**), you may offer an interactive opt-out: gate on **`command -v systemctl`** and the unit file (or an equivalent check), then **`promptYesNo`** (from **`src/prompt-yesno.sh`**, already pulled in via **`src/install-helpers.sh`** / **`./wsl-builder.sh`**) and on yes run **`sudo systemctl disable --now <unit>`** so the service stops immediately if running and does not start at boot. Multi-unit stacks (e.g. Docker Engine **`docker.service`**, **`docker.socket`**, **`containerd.service`**) keep explicit **`disable --now`** loops and stop ordering **in the component script**—do not add a generic **`src/`** helper until several installs share identical mechanics. **`promptYesNo`** on EOF/non-interactive stdin skips the disable (safe for CI). **Do not** add this without the user agreeing during that task—some daemons are meant to stay enabled. References: [`builds/ai/install_ollama.sh`](../../builds/ai/install_ollama.sh), [`builds/devops/install_docker.sh`](../../builds/devops/install_docker.sh), [`builds/db/install_mysql_server.sh`](../../builds/db/install_mysql_server.sh), [`builds/db/install_postgres_server.sh`](../../builds/db/install_postgres_server.sh). Document new prompts in the build’s **`README.md`**; new **`promptYesNo`** strings are user-visible—check **`test/`** / **`builds/test-fixture/`** for assertions.
- Use `getFile` for downloaded installers or binaries so files are cached via `CACHE_DIR`; call `cleanupGetFiles` after installers when cleanup is appropriate.
- **Large downloads / durable caches (user-configured paths):** besides `getFile` + `CACHE_DIR`, components may support optional variables in user **`wsl-builds.conf`** (sourced by **the builder** (`./wsl-builder.sh`) from **`WSL_BUILDS_CONF`** or **`~/.wsl-builds.conf`** before any `install_<component>.sh`) so users can park big artifacts on a Windows host path or another disk—reduces WSL VHD growth and preserves caches across distro rebuilds. Use **UPPER_SNAKE_CASE** names scoped to the tool (**`STYLEGAN3_PKL_CACHE`**, **`STYLEGAN3_PYTORCH_CACHE`**, **`OLLAMA_MODELS`**, etc.). In the install script, gate with **`[ -n "${VAR:-}" ]`** and wire the tool (conda `env config vars`, systemd `EnvironmentFile`, `mkdir`/`chown`, symlinks—whatever fits). Add **commented examples** to **`wsl-builds.conf.example`** whenever you introduce new optional keys; point end users at the build’s **`README.md`** for meaning. References: **`builds/ai-resources/install_sg3.sh`**, **`builds/ai/install_ollama.sh`**.
- **`src/install-dispatch.sh`** calls `recordComponentSuccess` after sourcing each `install_<component>.sh`; do not call it inside the component script.
- Assume `./wsl-builder.sh` exits on errors via `set -e`; do not add broad error swallowing.
- The **`builds/test-fixture/`** directory is **testing-only**: noop `install_<component>.sh` scripts and no production installs. See [`builds/test-fixture/README.md`](../../builds/test-fixture/README.md) and [`test/README.md`](../../test/README.md).
